name: Composite
description: A simple class for building hierarchies of documented entities.

name: id
description: A unique identifier of this composite among its siblings.

name: Documented
description: Mix-in interface for classess with documentation.

name: Duration
description: [Duration](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/time/Duration.html) is an amount of time in the [ISO-8601 Duration format](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601#Duration). Supports days and smaller units. Weeks, months and years are not supported. Example: ``P28DT10H``.

name: GitMarker
description: Marker with Git information such as a map of remotes.

name: headRefs
description: Refs on the head commit excluding the head itself. E.g. branch, tags.

name: remotes
description: A map of remote names to url's.

name: Instant
description:
[Instant](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/time/Instant.html) is a single instantaneous point on the time-line. 
If instant specification contains ``Z``, then it is parsed using [Instant.parse()](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/time/Instant.html#parse-java.lang.CharSequence-) method.
Otherwise the specification is used to construct ``java.util.Date`` which is then converted to instant.

Examples:

* ``2021-12-03T10:15:30.00Z`` - loaded using ``Instant.parse()``
* ``10/1/2021`` - loaded using ``new Date()`` and then converted to instant.

name: markers
description:
Markers pointing to where this model element was loaded from - location, line and column numbers. 
Multiple markers are supported for situations when a single model element is loaded from multiple locations, e.g. a row in an Excel document or a database and then pom.xml and readme.md is a source repository.
Another possiblity is an element being created from a prototype and then loaded - in this case the object will inherit markers from its prototype and will have a marker point to the location where it was loaded from.
Markers are listed in the reverse order, i.e. the prototype marker would be after the load marker in the list.

name: Marker
description: Provides information about location for a model element definition - URI, line and column numbers.

name: comment
description: Optional marker comment providing additional information about the marker. E.g. for locations which do not support lines and colums it may provide position inside the resource identified by the location attribute, such as an XPath for XML documents or sheet name and a range for Excel documents.

name: position
description: Marker position withing the resource identified by location - line and column in text documents, sheet and range in Excel, ...

name: ModelElement
description: Base class for many Nasdanika model classes.

name: uuid
description: Optional unique identifier for this model element. For root objects UUID is used to compute URI, if the URI is not set.

name: uris
description:
Element URI's - there might be more than one. See ``NcoreUtil.getUris()`` for more details.
URI's can be used for cross-referencing of elements in a resource-independent fashion.

name: labelPrototype
description:
If this reference is not set then EObjectLabelBuilder creates a new Label of its subclass (Link or Action) using AppFactory in newLabel() method. 
If this reference is set and is and instanceof Label then a copy of the label is created and returned.
Otherwise the reference value it is adapted to LabelProvider which is used to create a label. 
This allows to merge labels and chain label generation.

name: annotations
description: Annotations are used to store custom data similar to Java and Ecore annotations.

name: representations
description:
Mapping of representation keys to URI's of representation resources. URI's are resolved relative to the model element resource URI.
During object loading resources are loaded and linked to the object. Additional processing depends on the resource type.
In case of Drawio diagrams, diagram elements are semantically mapped to model elements and representation resource root elements are added as children to the object.
See [Nasdanika Core Drawio](../drawio/index.html) and [Nasdanika Core EMF](../emf/index.html) documentation for more information.

name: duration
description: Positive period duration in [ISO-8601 durations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601#Durations) format. E.g. ``P1M`` for one month or ``P20D`` for 20 days.

name: Reference
description: Object reference. May be used in containment collections to point to an object contained elsewhere.

name: RepresentationEntry
description: Mapping of representation key to a representation resource uri. Null values are supported to suppress inherited entries.

name: value
description: Representation resource URI. E.g. and URI of a Drawio diagram.

name: offset
description:
Time offset from the base in [ISO-8601 durations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601#Durations) format. 

Examples:

* ``P1H`` for one hour later.
* ``-P20D`` or ``P-20D`` for 20 days before. Can be null (zero), e.g. if one [period](Period.html) starts right after another period ends.

name: instant
description: An absolute point on the time-line. E.g. ``2021/07/04``.

name: minus
description:
Returns [duration](Duration.html) difference between this temporal and the argument temporal - how much this temporal is after the argument on the time-line, if difference can be computed, i.e. both this temporal and the argument temporal are instant or trace to the same base temporal. 
Returns null otherwise.

name: coincides
description: Tests if this temporal occurs at the same point on the time-line as the specified temporal. Returns null if unknown, i.e. two unrelated points in time.

name: minus
description: Returns a temporal based on this one offset by negation of the argument [duration](Duration.html). Null duration is treated as zero and set as-is (not negated).

name: normalize
description: Returns a normalized instance of this temporal not contained in the model. Normalization walks through the temporal chain from a temporal to its base to the root temporal. If that root temporal is instant/absolute then the normalized instance would be instant/absolute. Otherwise the normalized instance would contain the root temporal as its base and the offset would be the sum of all offsets.

name: copy
description: Returns a deep copy of self with bounds copied. Other containment references are not set.

name: before
description: Tests if this temporal is before the specified temporal. Returns null if unknown, i.e. two unrelated points in time.

name: after
description: Tests if this temporal is after the specified temporal. Returns null if unknown, i.e. two unrelated points in time.

name: plus
description: Returns a temporal based on this one offset by the argument [duration](Duration.html). Duration can be null - in this case it is treated as zero.

name: upperBounds
description: Upper bounds of a temporal. E.g. exact time of some temporal might not be known at a moment, but it might be known that it should not be after some other temporal - an upper bound. Upper bounds are used in validations and before/after computations.

name: lowerBounds
description: Lower bounds of a temporal. E.g. exact time of some temporal might not be known at a moment, but it might be known that it should not be before than some other temporal - a lower bound. Lower bounds are used in validations and before/after computations.

name: derivatives
description: Temporals which are based on this temporal.
